				\begin{document}$${\rm{Stock}}={\rm{\Sigma }}({C}_{i}\times bi\times di),$$\end{document}Stock=Σ(Ci×bi×di),where Ci is the concentration of Corg or Cinorg or N (in % DW divided by 100), bi is the dry bulk density (in g cm−3) and di is the sediment depth (in cm) of the sediment slice i. The stocks were converted to kg m−2 and Mg ha−1 to compare with similar studies.
